### CityVoice – Analytics API Tests
### Compatible with: IntelliJ HTTP Client, VS Code REST Client, kulala.nvim
### Base URL: http://localhost:8080/api
###
### ⚠ SETUP ORDER:
###   1. Run "0. Admin Login" → adminToken stored globally
###   2. Run tests in section order
###
### NOTE: All analytics endpoints require MANAGER or ADMIN roles.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@adminEmail = admin@cityvoice.vn
@adminPassword = Admin@123

# ─── 0. TOKEN SETUP ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 0. Admin login (stores adminToken globally)
# @name adminLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/staff/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}",
  "password": "{{adminPassword}}"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("adminToken", response.body.data.accessToken);
  client.test("Login OK",       () => client.assert(response.status === 200));
  client.test("Has accessToken",() => client.assert(response.body.data.accessToken !== ""));
%}


# ─── 1. HEATMAP ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1a. Get heatmap data (All reports)
GET {{baseUrl}}/analytics/heatmap
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

> {%
  client.test("Status 200",    () => client.assert(response.status === 200));
  client.test("Returns array", () => client.assert(Array.isArray(response.body.data)));
%}

###

### 1b. Get heatmap data (Filtered by Priority: high)
GET {{baseUrl}}/analytics/heatmap?priority=high
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 1c. Get heatmap data (Filtered by Date Range and Category)
# Note: Adjust dates and categoryId based on your database contents
GET {{baseUrl}}/analytics/heatmap?from=2023-01-01&to=2024-12-31&categoryId=1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


# ─── 2. AGGREGATED STATS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 2a. Get aggregated statistics (All reports)
GET {{baseUrl}}/analytics/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

> {%
  client.test("Status 200",          () => client.assert(response.status === 200));
  client.test("Has totalReports",    () => client.assert(response.body.data.totalReports !== undefined));
  client.test("Has completionRate",  () => client.assert(response.body.data.completionRate !== undefined));
%}

###

### 2b. Get aggregated statistics (Filtered by Zone)
# Note: Adjust zoneId based on your database contents
GET {{baseUrl}}/analytics/stats?zoneId=1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


# ─── 3. EXPORTS (EXCEL & PDF) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ⚠ NOTE: Downloading binary files via raw .http blocks can result in corrupted
# output depending on the HTTP client. 
# In IntelliJ: Right-click response window -> "Save as file"
# Or use the curl commands provided below.

### 3a. Export to Excel (All reports) - Returns binary .xlsx file
GET {{baseUrl}}/analytics/export/excel
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet

###
# curl -s -X GET http://localhost:8080/api/analytics/export/excel \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer $ADMIN_TOKEN" > reports_export.xlsx

### 3b. Export to Excel (Filtered by Priority: high)
GET {{baseUrl}}/analytics/export/excel?priority=high
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 3c. Export to PDF (All reports) - Returns binary .pdf file
GET {{baseUrl}}/analytics/export/pdf
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Accept: application/pdf

###
# curl -s -X GET http://localhost:8080/api/analytics/export/pdf \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer $ADMIN_TOKEN" > reports_export.pdf

### 3d. Export to PDF (Filtered by Date Range)
GET {{baseUrl}}/analytics/export/pdf?from=2023-01-01&to=2024-12-31
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
